Articles.Content:
Hi @Crzyrndm i noticed that you have recently shifted editing wing thickness from right click menu to holding  the button and dragging so pretty much as everything else

Would there still be a way to access those sliders (i mean wing tip thickness, wing root thickness etc. and i am talking Procedural Dynamics Wings not the B9 Pwing)
Sorry to interrupt but does this mod still have the ability to change wing thickness? It is quite important on some craft(s).

Hey!

This mod works absolutely wonderfull.

Except, when you drag the FAR mod into your gamedata folder.

Under FAR the procedural Dynamics wings produce nearly 0 (zero) lift. Although it does influence aerodynamics a bit since pitch control surfaces do effect the attitude. Yet control surface effect also is heavily reduced because I need to accelerate very fast before pitch control surfaces come into effect. The wings on my test craft are very large yet there is no aircraft to be seen, only a brick with wing looking surfaces.

edit: I just realized the control surfaces don't work at all, and there is probably zero lift being generated. The reason I had any pitch at all was either due to the cockpit reaction wheels. When I disable the reaction wheels it is a brick and just that.

This anomaly doesn't occur with stock aerodynamic parts so it's the Procedural Dynamics / FAR combo causing this on my RIG. Both mods including KSP are version 1.1.2
Another anomaly that occurs with procedural dynamics only with FAR installed is that if you attach a stock control surface to a procedural wing the aircraft becomes stuck in space (thus hangs on the runway.
I know it's the stock control surface + Pwing + FAR combo causing this because I removed every single part from my test plane and whenever that combo is introduced the airplane gets stuck in space. All it can do then is pitch up and down, but cant accelerate from a fixed point in space, roll or yaw.

I went through the thread replies for a few pages and can't find this being mentioned in either the FAR thread or this one.
But if this is a known issue I'll be awaiting to hear about it.

If not, is there a log file that can shed light on this, which one would be needed. Output.log doesn't read any errors at all. Nor does the player log.

EDIT:

I don't get it. I tried building a rocket power test rocket with Pwing attached and some stock control surfaces attached to it but now the bug does not occur. Whether I launch it from the VAB or SPH.

It seems to occur only on my test plane.

But whenever I try to rebuild that test plane with any design similar the bug reoccurs.
Begin to think off it, would this be a FAR bug and should I have posted in the FAR thread? The thing is, I don't know for sure which mod is the culprit. I only know the Far + PWing combo is causing the issue so sorry if this is purely related to FAR and in case of a bug I should submit it in the FAR thread.

2nd EDIT:

Here is the craft file.
You need Mechjeb, tweakscale, Proc parts and Pwing. And ofcourse FAR to introduce the bug.

Use stock control surfaces on the main wing and scratch your head.
Use Pcontrol surfaces and you have a brick but atleast the craft isn't stuck in space.

Edited June 12, 2016 by Vaporized Steel

Glad to see these back in business.. a lot of my designs depend on having P-Wings.
 

One thing though, maybe I missed it; but how do you change thickness? I know B9 wings have this, but sometimes it becomes tedious to use sliders for it, when it can easily be done with a key+mouse combo.

 

EDIT: Nevermind....figured it out.

Edited June 27, 2016 by Bloodbunny
"Doh" moment.
I added this mod to 1.1.3 and I cannot modify the wings. I hold B, T, or G and move my mouse over the wing and nothing happens. Running MM 2.6.23

3 hours ago, doormat said:

I added this mod to 1.1.3 and I cannot modify the wings. I hold B, T, or G and move my mouse over the wing and nothing happens. Running MM 2.6.23

Module Manager's most recent version is 2.6.25. Try removing the outdated MM version that you currently have installed and install MM 2.6.25.

I tried making a light-sport amphibious aircraft,  I think I failed on the "light" aspect.

This is the first time I've experienced this glitch and I had just downloaded the procedural wings mod and only that mod since the last time I played yesterday, so I'm assuming it's at fault.

In conjunction with the message in the center of the screen, the cost of the aircraft is displayed as "NaN".  Additionally, the CoM overlay cannot be seen when toggled even though the CoL and CoT overlays can be seen.

 

[edit]

After further investigation (I just ripped parts off), it turns out the offender was the vertical stab.

logs please...
Will this be updated? (Here comes my punishment from the mods even though I'm just asking )

1 hour ago, Murican_Jeb said:

Will this be updated? (Here comes my punishment from the mods even though I'm just asking )

The current version (11.1) has worked well for me thus far. And of course it will be updated... when it needs to be.

The current version (11.1) has worked well for me thus far. And of course it will be updated... when it needs to be.

Well, it still works, and the current version of ksp is 1.1.3

Just now, Murican_Jeb said:

Well, it still works, and the current version of ksp is 1.1.3

Umm... okay... my point exactly.

This mod is awesome and works under 1.1.3 (instead of B9 Aerospace Procedural Parts which is not) and recent FAR. 

I've found a minor bug however. This mod includes PWing - B9 SH and apparently something is wrong with it's model. FAR shows no reference area for that wing; other wings work ok.

I'm utterly poor modeller and only managed to import the model into blender and can not say what is wrong with it. Visually it looks pretty much like scaled up and rotated PWing - Mark 2, so I've replaced the B9 model with Mk2 model and tweaked the texture file - and this does the trick.

Here's B9 SH - Reference area is 1.22 m2 (area of booster actually)

 

This is Mk2 - Reference area is ok

 

Needless to say that B9 wing generates no lift.
What happened to adjusting the thickness? It isn't in the right click menu...
I just downloaded the latest version of this mod and can't seem to get the parts to expand at all. I've tried all the keybinds (t,g,b,o + mouseover)
